==Latin==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|la|grc|Œë||alpha}}, likely through Etruscan.

===Pronunciation===
* {{la-IPA|ƒÅ}}

===Letter===
{{head|la|letters|upper case||lower case|a}}

# {{lb|la|sometimes with ''[[littera]]''}} {{Latn-def|la|letter|1}}

====Usage notes====
* In compound words, long ''ƒÅ'' remains unchanged: {{m|la|labor|lƒÅbor}}, {{m|la|delabor|dƒìlƒÅbor}}; {{m|la|actus|ƒÅctus}}, {{m|la|peractus|perƒÅctus}}. In an internal syllable, short ''ƒÉ'' is changed by {{w|vowel reduction}} into short ''ƒ≠'' in open syllables and before /ng/, or short ''ƒï'' in closed ones and before /r/ and /l/: {{m|la|facio|faci≈ç}}, {{m|la|perficio|perfici≈ç}}, {{m|la|perfectus}}; {{m|la|tango|tang≈ç}}, {{m|la|contingo|conting≈ç}}; {{m|la|paro|par≈ç}}, {{m|la|impero|imper≈ç}}. It remains unchanged in cases in which the word was coined later on or levelled through analogy: {{m|la|amo|am≈ç}}, {{m|la|adamo|adam≈ç}}; {{m|la|patiens|patiƒìns}}, {{m|la|impatiens|impatiƒìns}}; {{m|la|tracto|tract≈ç}}, {{m|la|detrecto|dƒìtrect≈ç}}, later {{m|la|detracto|dƒìtract≈ç}}.

====Descendants====
* {{desc|nb|A}}

====See also====
* {{l|la|littera}}

===References===
* [http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/resolveform?type=exact&lookup=A&lang=latin A] in {{cite-book|author=Charlton T. Lewis|title=An Elementary Latin Dictionary|publisher=Harper & Brothers|location=New York|year=1891}}
: and in {{cite-book|author=Charlton T. Lewis and Charles Short|title=[[w:A Latin Dictionary|A Latin Dictionary]]|publisher=Clarendon Press|location=Oxford|year=1879}}

==Latvian==
{{wp|lv:}}

===Etymology===
Proposed in 1908 as part of the new Latvian spelling by the scientific commission headed by [[w:KƒÅrlis Mƒ´lenbahs|K. Mƒ´lenbahs]], which was accepted and began to be taught in schools in 1909. Prior to that, Latvian had been written in German [[Fraktur]], and sporadically in [[Cyrillic]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{lv-IPA|a}}
* {{audio|lv|lv-riga-a.ogg}}

