==Norwegian Bokm√•l==
{{wp|nb:}}

[[Image:Latin letter A.svg|250px|thumb|The [[letter]]  '''''A''''' from the [[Norwegian]] alphabet.]]

===Etymology===
From {{der|nb|la|A}}, from {{der|nb|grc|Œë||alpha}}, likely through the {{der|nb|ett|-}} language, from {{der|nb|phn|ê§Ä}}, from Proto-Canaanite [[Image:Protoalef.svg|20px]], from Proto-Sinaitic [[Image:Proto-semiticA-01.svg|20px]], from {{der|nb|egy|ìÉæ}} representing the head of an [[ox]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{sense|letter name}} {{IPA|nb|/…ëÀê/}}
* {{sense|phoneme}} {{IPA|nb|/a/|/…ëÀê/}}
* {{audio|nb|Pronunciation of Norwegian Bokm√•l ¬´A¬ª, ¬´a¬ª.ogg}}
* {{rhymes|nb|…ëÀê}}
* {{hyphenation|nb|A}}
* {{homophones|nb|a|√†|A-|a-|ah}}

===Letter===
{{head|nb|letters|upper case||lower case|a}}

# {{Latn-def|nb|letter|1}}

====See also====
{{list:Latin script letters/nb/simple}}

===Noun===
{{head|nb|nouns|g=m|definite singular|A-en|indefinite plural|A-er|definite plural|A-ene}}

# the letter {{l|nb|A}}
# {{lb|nb|horology}} symbol for {{l|nb|avance}}
# {{lb|nb|physics}} symbol for {{l|nb|ampere}}
