==Scots==

===Etymology 1===

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|sco|/…ëÀê/|/…îÀê/}}
* {{IPA|sco|/aÀê/|a=Northern,Insular}}

====Letter====
{{head|sco|letters|upper case||lower case|a}}

# {{Latn-def|sco|letter|1|aw}}

=====See also=====
{{list:Latin script letters/sco/simple}}

===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|sco|enm|a}}, an unstressed form of {{m|enm|I}}, itself a reduced form of {{m|enm|ik}}, {{m|enm|ic}}, from {{inh|sco|ang|ic}}, from {{inh|sco|gmw-pro|*ik}}, from {{inh|sco|gem-pro|*ek||pos=pronoun|I}}, from {{inh|sco|ine-pro|*e«µh‚ÇÇ√≥m}}.

====Alternative forms====
* {{alter|sco|A'|Aa|Ah|Aw}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|sco|/…ëÀê/|/…ë…™/|a=stressed}}
** {{IPA|sco|/…õÀê/|a=Dundee}} {{q|sometimes spelled {{m|sco|Eh}}}}
* {{IPA|sco|/…ô/|a=unstressed}}

====Pronoun====
{{head|sco|pronoun|cat2=personal pronouns}}

# [[I]] {{gloss|first-person singular pronoun}}

====See also====
{{Scots personal pronouns}}

