==Tagalog==

===Etymology 1===
{{bor+|tl|es|A}}. Each pronunciation has a different source:
* Filipino alphabet pronunciation is influenced by {{der|tl|en|A}}.
* Abakada alphabet pronunciation is influenced by [[Baybayin]] character {{m|tl|·úÄ}}.
* Abecedario pronunciation is from {{der|tl|es|A}}.

====Pronunciation====
{{tl-pr
|√©y<qq:letter name, Filipino alphabet>
|√°<qq:letter name, Abakada alphabet, Abecedario>
|-√°<qq:phoneme, stressed>
|-ƒÅ<qq:phoneme, unstressed>
|syll=A
}}

====Letter====
{{tl-letter}}

# {{tl-letter-def|1|ey|alph=fil}}
# {{tl-letter-def|1|a|alph=abak}}
# {{lb|tl|historical}} {{tl-letter-def|1|a|alph=abec}}

=====See also=====
{{list:Latin script letters/tl/simple}}

===Etymology 2===
Possibly short for {{m|tl|[[ama]] ([[ni]])}}.

====Pronunciation====
{{tl-pr}}

